quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  39,71,"And those who disbelieved will be driven to Hell in groups till when they reach it, the gates thereof will be opened. And its keepers will say: \"Did not the Messengers come to you from yourselves, reciting to you the Ayat of your Lord, and warning you of the meeting of this Day of yours\" They will say: \"Yes,\" but the Word of torment has been justified against the disbelievers"
  39,72,"It will be said: \"Enter you the gates of Hell, to abide therein. And what an evil abode of the arrogant"
  39,73,"And those who had Taqwa will be led to Paradise in groups till when they reach it, and its gates will be opened and its keepers will say: \"Salam `Alaykum (peace be upon you)! You have done well, so enter here to abide therein forever"
  39,74,"And they will say: \"All the praises and thanks be to Allah Who has fulfilled His promise to us and has made us inherit the land. We can dwell in Paradise where we will; how excellent a reward for the workers"
  39,75,"And you will see the angels surrounding the Throne from all round, glorifying the praises of their Lord. And they will be judged with truth. And it will be said, \"All the praises and thanks be to Allah, the Lord of all that exits"